  "text": "Proof: See Appendix E. The above result relies on the assumption that satisfies the conditions discussed above. The following proposition states that this assumption holds for the popular max-degree weight design scheme [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . The max-degree weights are very simple to compute and are well suited for distributed implementation. In order to determine the weights, the nodes need no information beyond their number of neighbors.",
